The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | United okay with Ronaldos Real deal
                                                                                                                                                                                                     United okay with Ronaldos Real deal
            IN amp; OUT                
	 Manchester Uniteds owners, the Glazer family, are set to enter negotiations with Real Madrid for Cristiano Ronaldo, according to reports. A Spanish newspaper on Wednesday claimed that sources close to the Americans, who bought the Old Trafford club in 2004, said that the Glazers have agreed to the operation, fearing Ronaldos value will decrease if they hold onto him.         
	Inter close in         
	 Frank Lampards proposed transfer to Inter Milan moved closer on Tuesday night after reports from Italy suggested that the England midfielder would make a decision on his future within the next 24 hours.         
	In another significant development, Jose Mourinho made his first signing as Inter manager with the arrival of Brazilian international Amantino Mancini, a player who Mourinho believes would be the perfect foil for Lampard.         
	Podolski for EPL         
	 Bayern Munich striker Lukas Podolski may join Tottenham Hotspur or Manchester City. The German has been among the goals of late. But he was embroiled in war of words with Bayern and is certain to leave.         
	Silva England bound         
	 Spanish winger David Silva is likely to join either Arsenal or Liverpool. He has outshone more celebrated colleagues with his busy, skill-intensive play, scoring the memorable third goal against Russia in the semi-final of Euro 2008.         
	Newcastle eye Aimar         
	 Newcastle hope to complete the signing of Pablo Aimar from Real Zaragoza in the next 48 hours.         
	Bridge retained         
	 Wayne Bridges new contract at Chelsea will be worth 16.6 million over four years as manager Luiz Felipe Scolari has made keeping the left-back at Stamford Bridge one of his top priorities.         
	Berbatov uncertain         
	 Striker Dimitar Berbatov faces an anxious wait over his future after Tottenham Hotspur indicated that they do not intend to negotiate with Manchester United or any other club.                                                                                                                            
